# Compiled Go binaries
# This ignores a binary named after your module if you ever run `go build`
url-shortener
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*.test

# Output of the go coverage tool
*.out

# Our local "database" file - this should NEVER be committed.
# Each environment (yours, a teammate's, production) should have its own.
urls.json

# Go workspace file (if you ever use `go work`)
go.work
go.work.sum

# OS-specific junk files
.DS_Store